Package gov.sandia.gmp.util.containers.tree.sets

Class TreeSetDouble

java.lang.Object
gov.sandia.gmp.util.containers.tree.TreeIntrinsic
gov.sandia.gmp.util.containers.tree.sets.TreeSetDouble
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class TreeSetDouble extends TreeIntrinsic
A Red-Black tree based intrinsic Double set implementation. This set is sorted on the intrinsic key from smallest to largest in the tree.

This implementation provides guaranteed log(n) time cost for the contains, get, add and remove operations. Algorithms are adaptations of those in Cormen, Leiserson, and Rivest's Introduction to Algorithms.

Note that this implementation is not synchronized. If multiple threads access a map concurrently, and at least one of the threads modifies the map structurally, it must be synchronized externally. (A structural modification is any operation that adds or deletes one or more mappings; merely changing the value associated with an existing key is not a structural modification.) This is typically accomplished by synchronizing on some object that naturally encapsulates the set.
